
 Program flow:

 	Handling -c option. Option should followed by vars file name.

	Handling -p option. Option should followed by proxy address.

	Source vars file.

	Reset logs file location.
	LOG_DIR specifies a directory where logs are stored.
	INSTALL_LOG holds stdout output.
	ERROR_LOG holds a stderr output.

	Searches for any VAR=VAL pair found on command line. VAR will be set to value and used in
	program in addition to variables found in vars file.

	Install and enable ntp server.

	Purges log files if any data was found.

	
